<section class="container">
  <h2><code>\{{input-date}}</code></h2>
  <p>
    The <code>\{{input-date}}</code> works well if it is bound to one of your model's
    <code>DS.attr('date')</code> attribute. A user begins by typing a date and then
    presses enter. The text box's parser will attempt to create a date from the input.
    Use <strong>English</strong> phrases or abbreviated dates like:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><em>today</em></li>
    <li><em>now</em></li>
    <li><em>yesterday</em></li>
    <li><em>mar 1</em></li>
    <li><em>last week</em></li>
    <li><em>sep 9 1977</em></li>
  </ul>
  <p>...and the list goes on and on. Enjoy.</p>
</section>

